column144: I wouldn't say there was necessarily anything unusual that would be present here. It occurred to me that the situation was very nearly a prisoner's dilemma although not quite entirely so (if someone defects
column145: their payoff is always the same regardless of the other guy's choice here
column146: while in a true prisoner's dilemma it would have been higher had the other guy cooperated)
column147: but I wouldn't say that really mattered here because the questions themselves were stuff like whether or not yellow would be angry over what happened rather than something like whether or not purple's actions were appropriate or something
column148: which is a completely different way of asking about everything that's more detached from my own personal feelings on the matter."
